products.name: Gerber Cereal for Baby 1st Foods Single Grain Cereal Oatmeal

extendedInfo.detail: 11 grams of whole grains per serving.  60% of DV of iron for learning-ability.  Non GMO Project verified. nongmoproject.org.  No. 1 pediatricians recommended brand (Among pediatricians who recommend infant cereal) for infant cereals. Supported Sitter. 1st Foods. Grain & Grow brings the goodness of whole grains and tailored nutrition. Iron to support brain development & learning ability. Gerber combines high quality whole grain goodness with 12 essential nutrients. We take action to protect the planet - so Gerber babies will grow and thrive for generations to come. Supported Sitter: Your baby may be ready for this cereal if they: Sit with support; On tummy, push up arms with straight elbows; Lean towards spoon with an open mouth. This package is sold by weight, not volume, and may not appear full due to settling of contents. Every bite counts! Learn more.  Visit Gerber.com to chat with a MyGerber Baby Expert 1-800-4-Gerber; 24/7. Visit Gerber.com/sustainability to learn more.
extendedInfo.ingredients: Whole Grain Oat Flour And Oat Flour (Contains Wheat), Potassium Phosphate, Vitamins And Minerals: Calcium Carbonate, Vitamin C (Ascorbic Acid), Iron (Electrolytic), Zinc Sulfate, Vitamin E (Alpha Tocopheryl Acetate), Niacinamide, Vitamin B2 (Riboflavin), Vitamin B1 (Thiamin Mononitrate), Vitamin B6 (Pyridoxine Hydrochloride), Folic Acid, Vitamin B12.
extendedInfo.directions: Easy-to-Mix Directions: 1. Pour desired amount of cereal in bowl. 2. Stir in liquid (breastmilk or infant formula) to desired consistency. Serve as is or warm in the microwave. Always test temperature before feeding. Discard any unfed cereal. Completely cooked and ready to serve. Just add liquid. Mix! Baby's first cereal. Mix 1 tbsp. cereal with 4-5 tbsp. of breastmilk or infant formula.  Microwave: Microwave Guidelines for Heating: Warm unheated liquid at medium (50% power) for 15-30 seconds. Mix heated liquid with cereal. Stir to even out temperature. Test temperature before feeding.  Store in a cool, dry place. Use within 30 days after opening.  Twist cap off, remove seal & twist back on.
extendedInfo.warnings: Contains: wheat.Do not use if seal is damaged. Keep container dry. Keep package away from children.
